\newpage
\chapter{Implementation}

This chapter outlines the step-by-step development process followed to create the web-based mini-game platform.

\section{Development Methodology}
The project followed an iterative development model:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Planning:} Defining game features and UI components.
    \item \textbf{Design:} Wireframing the interface and preparing game logic flowcharts.
    \item \textbf{Implementation:} Writing HTML, CSS, and JavaScript code for each game.
    \item \textbf{Testing:} Conducting unit and integration testing.
    \item \textbf{Review:} Validating game behavior and refining design.
\end{itemize}

\section{Front-End Development}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Created user interfaces using \textbf{HTML5} and \textbf{CSS3}.
    \item Developed interactive behaviors using \textbf{JavaScript}:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Simon Game: Color/sound sequence generator and user response validation.
        \item Dice Game: Random dice rolling with Math.random().
        \item Tic-Tac-Toe: 3x3 grid with win-checking logic.
        \item Drum Kit: Keyboard and mouse event listeners triggering audio.
    \end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

\section{Back-End Development}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Used \textbf{Node.js} as the runtime for executing server-side JavaScript.
    \item Implemented the web server using \textbf{Express.js}:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Define game routes.
        \item Serve static assets.
        \item Render dynamic views using \textbf{EJS}.
    \end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

\section{Testing and Debugging}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Manual testing was performed for each game to check:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Input handling
        \item Game reset and replay functionality
        \item Win/lose conditions
        \item Browser responsiveness
    \end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

\section{Challenges Faced}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Synchronizing animations and sound in the Simon and Drum games.
    \item Managing user turns and draw/win logic in Tic-Tac-Toe.
    \item Ensuring cross-browser compatibility and responsive layout design.
\end{itemize}

